The article is a statement from President Joseph R. Biden Jr. paying tribute to General Colin Powell, who recently passed away. General Powell is described as a patriot of unmatched honor and dignity, who rose to the highest ranks of the United States military and advised four Presidents. He is praised for embodying the highest ideals of both a warrior and a diplomat, and for breaking racial barriers throughout his life. President Biden considers General Powell a good friend and a great American, and orders that flags be flown at half-staff to honor his life of service to the nation. The statement is signed by President Biden on October 18, 2021.